 Privacy Policy for ShiftTrak

  Effective Date: January 2025Last Updated: January 2025

  Introduction

  TJXLABS ("we", "our", or "us") operates the ShiftTrak mobile application (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our App.

  Our Commitment: ShiftTrak is designed with privacy as a core principle. Your personal work data stays on your device and is never uploaded to our servers.

  ---
  Information We Collect

  1. Information You Provide

  When you use ShiftTrak, you may enter:
  - Work shift details (dates, times, locations)
  - Earnings information (wage rates, pay amounts)
  - Employment details (job titles, employer names - optional)
  - Tags and notes (custom labels you create)
  - Photos (receipts, rosters, or other images you attach to shifts)

  2. Automatically Collected Information

  - Crash and diagnostic data - Anonymous error reports sent via Firebase Crashlytics to help us fix bugs and improve app stability
  - Device information - Device model, Android version (only collected during crashes)

  ---
  How We Store Your Information

  Local Storage

  - All your personal data is stored locally on your device using SQLite database
  - Your shift data, earnings, photos, and settings never leave your device
  - We do not have access to your personal information
  - We do not store your data on any cloud servers
  - We do not have servers or databases that collect user data

  Third-Party Services

  We use Firebase Crashlytics (by Google) for crash reporting:
  - Collects anonymous crash logs when the app encounters errors
  - Does not include your shift data, earnings, or personal information
  - Helps us identify and fix bugs
  - You can learn more at https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          

  ---
  How We Use Your Information

  - Your shift data is used only by you, on your device, to track your work hours and earnings
  - Crash reports help us fix bugs and improve app performance
  - We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties
  - We do not use your data for advertising or marketing

  ---
  Data Sharing and Disclosure

  We do not share your personal information with anyone, except:
  - Firebase Crashlytics receives anonymous crash reports (no personal data)
  - As required by law if legally compelled to disclose information

  We will never:
  - Sell your data to third parties
  - Use your data for advertising
  - Share your shift or earnings information with anyone

  ---
  Your Rights and Choices

  You have complete control over your data:

  Access and Export

  - View all your data within the app
  - Export your data as PDF or CSV files (PRO feature)

  Data Deletion

  - Delete individual shifts from the shift details screen
  - Clear all app data by uninstalling the app or using Android Settings > Apps > ShiftTrak > Clear Data
  - Once deleted, data cannot be recovered (we don't have backups - it's only on your device)

  Crash Reporting

  - Crash reporting is enabled by default to help improve the app
  - You cannot opt-out while using the app, but crash reports contain no personal data

  ---
  Children's Privacy

  ShiftTrak is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided information to us, please contact us.

  ---
  Data Security

  - All data is stored securely on your device using SQLite database
  - We implement industry-standard security practices in our code
  - Your device's built-in security (lock screen, encryption) protects your data
  - We do not transmit your personal data over the internet

  ---
  Changes to This Policy

  We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted:
  - In the app (About screen)
  - On this page with an updated "Last Updated" date

  Continued use of the app after changes means you accept the updated policy.

  ---
  Contact Us

  If you have questions about this Privacy Policy:

  Developer: TJXLABSEmail: (tjxlabs@gmail.com) Location: Australia

  ---
  Summary (TL;DR)

  ✅ Your data stays on your device - We don't have servers or cloud storage✅ No account required - No sign-ups, no emails✅ No tracking - We don't track your usage or behavior✅ Anonymous crash reports only - Helps us fix bugs, contains no personal data✅ No ads - We don't collect data for
  advertising✅ Full control - You can export or delete your data anytime

